    <text>
        <front>
            <div type="summary">
                <p>
                    Virginia Woolf wrote to Miss Perkins in hopes of still making the corrections to Roger Fry as she had agreed to Pierpont Morgan's son, and asked about her life in Letchworth.
                </p>
            </div>
        </front>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date when="1940-11-25">
                            25th Nov. 1940
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>
                        Dear <persName>Miss Perkins</persName><note><p>The person is unidentifiable from Wikidata and further investigation.</p></note>,
                    </salute>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    I see from an advertisement yesterday in the <lb/>
                    <orgName key="Q221986">Sunday Times</orgName> that a third impression of 
                    <choice>
                        <orig><title>Roger Fry</title></orig>
                        <reg><title>Roger Fry: A Biography</title></reg>
                    </choice> is <lb/>
                    being prepared. I wish I had known before. I hope <lb/>
                    there is still time to make the corrections I enclose <lb/>
                    on this page.
                </p>
                <p>
                    There are two others that I have had to <lb/>
                    agree to make, owing to an appeal from <lb/>
                    <choice>
                        <orig><persName key="Q54168">Pierpont Morgan</persName></orig>
                        <reg><persName key="Q54168">John Pierpont Morgan</persName></reg>
                    </choice>
                    's son<note><p>Pierpont Morgan's son refers to <persName key="Q174774">John Pierpont Morgan Jr.</persName></p></note>. These are: <lb/>
                    to delete on page 140 (near the beginning) <lb/>
                    the senetnce that begins "I knew the answer beforehand..." <lb/>
                    and to delete on page 144 (in the middle) the <lb/>
                    senetnnce beginning "I always wondered...."
                </p>
                <p>
                    I hope this is clear.
                </p>
                <p>
                    I wonder how you like <placeName>Letchworth</placeName>? It seems an age since <lb/>
                    we saw you and <persName>Miss Griffiths</persName><note><p>The person is unidentifiable from Wikidata and further investigation.</p></note>. We are having to <lb/>
                    bring down all the furniture in the flat, as it is <lb/>
                    getting waterlogged. What a bore it all is-- <lb/>
                    Here we have had a tremendous flood, owing to a <lb/>
                    bomb bursting the river bank. And the usual <lb/>
                    Excitements of seeing planes shot down.
                </p>
                <p>
                    I hope you and <persName>Miss Griffiths</persName> will come here <lb/>
                    if you ever want --well, I cant say its exactly a <lb/>
                    peaceful place. But we dont get bombs at night.
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>
                        Yours sincerely
                    </salute>
                    <signed>
                        Virginia Woolf
                    </signed>
                    <placeName>
                        Monks House, Rodmell, Lewes.
                    </placeName>
                    <seg>
                        <!-- post scriptum -->
                    </seg>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
